---
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>The Agile Architecture Lab | AgileTactix</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="An ongoing workspace for Agile professionals who want to move beyond managing ceremonies and begin building delivery systems that operate reliably."
    />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/favicon.png" />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/favicon.png" />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-[#1a1a1a] antialiased">
    <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <section class="text-center space-y-6 mb-16">
        <img
          src="/favicon.png"
          alt="AgileTactix icon"
          class="mx-auto w-16"
        />
        <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-[#1a1a1a]">
          The Agile Architecture Lab
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl sm:text-2xl text-[#444444]">
          Stop coordinating work. Start designing how delivery runs.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1a1a1a] leading-relaxed">
          The Agile Architecture Lab is an ongoing workspace for Agile
          professionals who want to move beyond managing ceremonies and begin
          building delivery systems that operate reliably without constant
          manual intervention.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg text-[#1a1a1a] leading-relaxed">
          You will learn how automation, communication flow, and reporting
          structures work together so a team can function predictably — even
          when you are not actively managing every step.
        </p>
        <div>
          <a
            href="https://agiletactix.mysamcart.com/checkout/the-agile-architecture-lab-founding-members"
            class="inline-block bg-[#294bf3] text-white font-semibold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#1e3acc] transition-colors"
          >
            Join the Agile Architecture Lab — Founding Members
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Why this exists -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">Why this exists</h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Many Agile roles are built around coordination: meetings, reminders,
          and manual follow-ups.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          That works when teams are small and stable.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          But in larger organizations, coordination alone does not scale.
          If the process only works because a person constantly pushes it
          forward, that role becomes difficult to justify and hard to grow.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The professionals who become valuable over time are not the ones who
          attend more ceremonies — they are the ones who design how delivery
          works.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The Agile Architecture Lab teaches you how to create systems that
          keep work moving, create visibility automatically, and reduce
          dependence on constant oversight.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The benefit is not just efficiency.
          It is professional leverage.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Transformation -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">
          What actually changes
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Many teams rely on constant personal effort: reminders, manual
          updates, and repeated explanations. Work progresses because someone
          continuously monitors and pushes it forward.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          That creates hidden pressure.
          The system depends on attention rather than structure.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium">
          Inside the Lab, the focus shifts from effort to design.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Instead of personally carrying the process, you build a process that
          carries the work.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          You will learn how to implement:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg pl-6 list-disc marker:text-[#294bf3]">
          <li>automated sprint start and closure behavior</li>
          <li>consistent stakeholder visibility</li>
          <li>reporting that generates itself</li>
          <li>safeguards that surface problems early</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The goal is not more tools.
          The goal is a delivery process that runs predictably.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Who This Is For -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">Who This Is For</h2>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg pl-6 list-disc marker:text-[#294bf3]">
          <li>Scrum Masters who want less manual coordination</li>
          <li>Individual contributors seeking technical leverage</li>
          <li>Agile practitioners responsible for team visibility</li>
          <li>Professionals who want durable, repeatable processes</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Inside the Lab -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">Inside the Lab</h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The Lab focuses on systems rather than isolated automations.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          You will work through how multiple automations interact to create a
          repeatable delivery lifecycle.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          You will implement:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg pl-6 list-disc marker:text-[#294bf3]">
          <li>sprint lifecycle automation</li>
          <li>stakeholder communication structures</li>
          <li>automated reporting workflows</li>
          <li>escalation safeguards for stalled work</li>
          <li>structured operational reviews</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          New material is added as systems evolve and real delivery problems
          are solved.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Positioning with Kit -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">
          How this relates to the Automation Kit
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The Sprint Automation Kit shows how to implement individual
          automation rules.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The Agile Architecture Lab explains how those rules fit together
          into an operating system for delivery.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          You move from isolated improvements to a designed workflow — where
          communication, visibility, and reporting no longer depend on manual
          coordination.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The kit helps you automate tasks.
          The Lab helps you design the environment those tasks operate within.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Founding Members -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">
          Founding Members
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          The current enrollment is the initial founding cohort.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">Founding members receive:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-lg pl-6 list-disc marker:text-[#294bf3]">
          <li>lifetime access</li>
          <li>all future system additions</li>
          <li>updates as the Lab evolves</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          This program will later transition into a structured membership.
          Founding members keep permanent access.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Closing -->
      <section class="space-y-6 mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">
          What this leads to
        </h2>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          When delivery depends on constant coordination, your value is tied
          to your presence. If you step away, the process slows down.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          When delivery depends on systems, your value is tied to how the work
          operates.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          You are no longer measured by how much you personally manage, but by
          how reliably the team functions.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          Many Agile careers plateau because they remain inside facilitation
          and oversight.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
          This Lab exists to teach the skills that move beyond that —
          designing processes, not just supporting them.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <section
        class="bg-[#f0f7ff] border border-[#294bf3]/20 rounded-xl px-8 py-12 text-center space-y-6"
      >
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#294bf3]">
          Join the Agile Architecture Lab — Founding Members
        </h2>
        <p class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a]">
          $197
          <span class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-normal text-[#444444]">
            one-time access
          </span>
        </p>
        <div>
          <a
            href="https://agiletactix.mysamcart.com/checkout/the-agile-architecture-lab-founding-members"
            class="inline-block bg-[#294bf3] text-white font-semibold text-lg px-8 py-4 rounded-lg hover:bg-[#1e3acc] transition-colors"
          >
            Join the Agile Architecture Lab — Founding Members
          </a>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-[#666666]">
          30-day refund if it's not a fit.
        </p>
      </section>

    </main>
  </body>
</html>
